<br />

<br />
To complain about complaining is self destructive behavior in itself.
<br />
Does it make sense? I think not <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Anyways, this is what I have said and will say. You will not hear me
<br />
complain about any 'nerf' 
<br />
IMO, if you have the skill, have 'what it takes' per se, then you will
<br />
have the ability to play your class with perfection in any situation you
<br />
are put into. 
<br />

<br />
If you need to be 'over-powered' or need the extended durations of
<br />
so many things to be <span style="font-style: italic">powerful</span> or just to flat out <span style="font-style: italic">save your own ass, 
<br />
and asses of others</span>,  then might I suggest playing another class.
<br />

<br />
I don't exactly think it is 'whining' I think it is you get used to something,
<br />
you use it and you are content, content even knowing it is, in fact, a toy
<br />
that we should not be given. I am saying this because I will be the first 
<br />
to take anything that is 'over- powered' and use it to my full advantage.
<br />
I know that I am not alone on this, and the other people who do know 
<br />
what to do when given such a wonderful toy understand this. 
<br />

<br />
We were given a tad too much 'unf' and it should have been made more
<br />
risky. It was already risk vs reward, but saying "well, my 500+dps pet
<br />
rips ass when charm breaks, so you shouldnt nerf it based on that"
<br />
Well, my green con dire charm pet has done some 'ass ripping' itself. 
<br />

<br />
It was too easy, was always risky but the risk seems to have more of
<br />
a balance vs how it was before. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, pointing at the enchanter who cried nerf  is a waste, really.
<br />
Yea, I was sad cus I couldnt charm something, give it a nice mage 
<br />
set up, sov, ndt, virtue, fos, etc and send it on a few mobs, toss a dot
<br />
on them.. go afk for a smoke break and come back with some +20% axp. 
<br />
Who in the hell would not be sad?!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="icon_lol.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Nothing will change about whiners, it is like expecting a monk to forget
<br />
about their first big 'nerf'..deal with it.
<br />

<br />
