                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Before creating my chanter I looked at all the classes spells and abilities to pick the class I wanted. The chanter's charm was very attractive to me and is a major reason I created him. Now I can solo charm in places like PoF for 2%xp (less than i'd get soloing the skellies in PoV, i consider it a complete waste of time considering the deaths and danger), about half of what i'll get in a good group . If only there were peeps in elementals to group with in the day when I'm on it wouldnt be so bad. We are powerfull when it come to mez but are the weakest of the weak when it's time to damage and kill mobs. The pet might but he will take most of the xp unless you outdage him (like that is going to happen). So I dont play during the afternoon much anymore (I am so sick of BoT) and raid in the evening.
<br />

<br />
So yes charm is a big disapointment, it's not like we never had it, we did, we became chanters because of it and they took it away. I dont solo except greenies for tradeskills components or quests (talk about excitement). I you like grouping, mezzing and buffing then you should enjoy the chanter class, if you'd like to solo and take an offensive stance then i'd recommend you pick another class.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
