                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Back in january we were:
<br />
- The best crowd controllers in 95% of the world's zones
<br />
- One of the best buffing classes in the game, with several unique buffs
<br />
- One of the three most wanted group classes
<br />
- Tied for the best soloing class in the game
<br />
- The most damage dealing class in a group and/or raid
<br />

<br />

<br />
You think that was fair? Yeah, charm was always powerful. But with the insane damage output of PoP mobs it became truly sick. Besides, back in the day, good charming was actually a rather well kept secret. Very few chanters did it, even if they could. When something is not heavily abused, it rarely gets nerfed. With PoP, word started spreading... first among some chanters, who started taking advantage of our overpowered situation... then to other classes who started whining about it, in turn getting more enchanters to charm, which in turn caused more people to whine, etc. It got louder and louder until SOE put the smackdown on us. The first few weeks the chanter boards were chock full of whining chanters saying their abilites were now useless, while a few kept at it and still killed faster than groups. Even after the exp changes in June, I exp a lot faster charming than grouping (admittedly at 5<img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" />, and most experienced 65 enchanters I talk to do so as well.
<br />

<br />
If you ask me, charm is balanced now. Heck, our class is still very powerful apart from one major downfall - our uselessness in numbers on raids. With more and more of the game concentrating on raiding, this is becoming an issue that could use looking at, but there are several classes that are WAY worse off than us.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2212" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.elerion.net/pics/sjhosig.jpg" border="0" /></a><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">
<br />
"Carrot Cake Soup is like the taste of watching girls make out. It has an extraordinary power that oscillates between gentle and overwhelming, between light and dark, between pleasure and more pleasure." - Penny Arcade</span></span></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
