                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charming became far too easy in POP ... it was always overpowering however it was overpowering and required skill in previous expansions <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
In every single expansion to date I have been able to outdamage my entire party with charm upon release.  I can still do so in POP and in LDoN.
<br />

<br />
They nerfed charm in some way shape or form in almost every expansion as well.
<br />

<br />
1. Release the expansion
<br />
2. Under equiped character complain that enchanters do far too much damage using charm.
<br />
3. SOE nerfs charm
<br />
4. Other characters gear up and find enchanter pets are not too bad when compared to fully expansion geared characters.
<br />

<br />
Although, LDoN was the first expansion that charm came pre-nerfed <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  However, that said ... I am sure it will be nerfed again in some fashion because a wolf quadding for 900 more than outdamages my entire group and is "reasonably" easy to control.
<br />

<br />
So, I expect people will complain once they realize they need enchanters with charm or a heavy DPS group to complete the hard missions and the nerf bat will fall like it always does on the enchanters.
<br />

<br />
As for me, I have almost always gotten XP faster in a good group than I have soloing with charm ... fortunately I have access to a good group <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Regards,</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370213" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zanithar TideBreaker</a> - Coercer
<br />
